Dendrocalamus longispathus

    Authority
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5235

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   A large tufted bamboo with culms reachin 13-20 m in height and 7.5-10
   cm in diameter.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial bamboo.
   COMMON NAMES
   Khang, Ora, Waya, Wanet, Talagu-wa.
   FURTHER INF
   Khang is native of Myanmar. Bamboos grow between the latitudes 40°N and
   S. Though the big bamboo forests usually occur between 15-25°N and S.

   Sources
   SOURCES (D. longispathus Kurz.)
   Troup R 1921 pp 1009 [DRA, FER, TEXT]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 427 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 14 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Hassan M 1988 pp 505-513 [RAIN, TEMP, SAL, DRA, TEXT, PH, DEP]

